</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN — 4156 Lamp of Our Feet (G major, 3/4)
Key: G (1 sharp F#). Lilting 3/4 waltz character.

Non-diatonic subs: A7 → Am (ii); F#ø7 → Em (vi) or C (IV);
G# (=Ab) → C (IV); C# → D (V, approach note).

Rhythmic variety: 3/4 lends itself to dotted-half sustained chords
in melodic peak measures (4,7,11,14) and quarter-note arpeggio motion
in active measures (3,5,10,12). Moving quarter notes in LH create
waltz-bass feel in mm.1,2,5,6.

TEXTURE ARC:
mm.1-4: Open entry I/ii/V, light 2-note RH, gentle LH
mm.5-7: V section builds then releases on D (m.7 sustained)
mm.8-11: Modal middle section with Am/C color, builds to D climax (m.11)
mm.12-14: Final cadence I→IV→I→V7→I. D7 "333" in m.13 creates pull to final G.
-->
